          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-16 11:03:20" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>long legless reptile; no eyelids or external ears; moves by wriggling or gliding; some species have a poisonous bite; symbol of lurking, unexpected danger; associated with lies, deception, and misleading teaching</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>snake</Gloss>
                <Gloss>reptile</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though ὄφις[a] may refer to any kind of snake, in {S:04201001900018} it is obviously a reference to a poisonous snake that would harm a person who stepped on it. In translating {S:04201001900018} it is essential to avoid an expression which will mean merely ‘to walk on snakes’ as though one were to walk for some distance over a mass of swarming snakes. The implication of this context is simply that one is able to step on snakes without being harmed.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
