          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-16 11:03:20" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of {L:ὄφις&lt;SDBG:ὄφις:000000&gt;}[a] snake, {D:4.52}) a dangerous and despised person</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>evil person</Gloss>
                <Gloss>viper</Gloss>
                <Gloss>snake</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>One must exercise due caution in rendering ἔχιδνα in {S:04001203400004} and ὄφις in {S:04002303300002}, since in some cultures snakes are regarded as being particularly wise and clever, and therefore an expression such as ‘brood of vipers’ could be a compliment. In some languages important distinctions are made between different types of snakes, and therefore connotations may vary considerably.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
